			Arthmetic Operators:

note: bash shell dont have any mechanisam to perform simple arthemetic operations, but it uses external programs eiter AWK or XPR
+ additional -- it adds values on either side of thr operator

eg: 
a=5
b=10
'expr $a + $b'

- substraction
subtracts right hand operand from left hand operand

echo 'expr $a - $b'

* multiplication
multiplies values on either side of operators

echo 'expr $a \* $b'

/ division
divides left hand operand by right hand operand

echo 'expr $b / $a'

% modulers
divides left hand operand by right hand operand and returns the remainder

echo 'expr $b % $a'

= assignment operator
Assigns right hans operand in left hand opernad

a=$b

== equality
it compares two numbers if both are same then it returns true

!= not equality

note: []
all conditional exp should be inside square brases with spaces around them
[ $a == $b ]
